#spec #design #built

> Notes can be organised into subdirectories within eshp/ — BUILT.

## What changed

Slugs are now root-relative POSIX paths without .eshp extension.

  eshp/store.eshp           → slug: store           (top-level, unchanged)
  eshp/concepts/auth.eshp   → slug: concepts/auth
  eshp/modules/api.eshp     → slug: modules/api

Always `/` separator (POSIX), even on Windows. No DB schema change — slugs are plain TEXT.
Top-level notes are fully backward compatible.

## How it works

  eshp_parser.py  parse_eshp(path, root=None)
    When root is given: slug = path.relative_to(root).as_posix().removesuffix(".eshp")
    When root is None:  slug = path.stem  (backward-compat default)

  eshp_store.py   sync() uses rglob("*.eshp") and passes root=self.root to parse_eshp

  eshp_cli.py     EshpHandler derives slug via path.relative_to(store.root).as_posix()
                  Both watchdogs run recursive=True
                  eshp new concepts/auth  creates parent dirs automatically

## Key rule

Relationship references must always use the FULL path-slug:
  -> concepts/auth       ✓  refers to eshp/concepts/auth.eshp
  -> auth                ✗  will be a dangling edge (ghost node) if no eshp/auth.eshp exists

## Out of scope

Relative refs (-> ./sibling), ambiguous short-slug resolution, .eshpignore, rename/move tooling.

